# Critical extraction note: watib uses **Bigloo
# `?VARNAME` match-case pattern-variable for arg
# capture** at watib.scm:49 et seq — `(("--stop-
# after" ?n (help "...")) (set! keep-going
# (string->number n)))`.  The `?n` syntax (from
# Bigloo's MATCH-CASE macros) BINDS the next
# argv element to the symbol `n` for use in the
# body.  Distinct from R311 Guile `(value #t)`
# keyword arg-shape, R313 Idris 2 `NoArg ctor` /
# `ReqArg ctor "<plc>"` constructor variants,
# R324 Chicken `#:required` keyword.  Bigloo's
# approach: `?VARNAME` PATTERN VARIABLE for arg
# capture — corpus's **first documented match-
# case-pattern-variable-for-arg-capture CLI
# pattern**.
